<s> Expect criticism if you top-post  </s>
<s> Personae are great.  </s>
<s> But you need a lot of them to cover the great variety of disability type, degree, onset etc that represent the variety of abilities and skills of these different users.  </s>
<s> No. By definition we're not trying for maximum inclusion; personae are models.  </s>
<s> We merely need a reasonable cross-section of WCAG 2.0 target groups.  </s>
<s> Personae are an adjunct to other methods of usability testing and are not the sole such method.  </s>
<s> If you leave a certain category out of personae, you can test for usability for that category elsewhere.  </s>
<s> Merely as an example, it would probably be overkill to produce six persone for colour deficiency (protan, anomalous protan, deutan, anomalous deutan, tritan, and the one everybody fixates on that's almost impossible to find, achromat).  </s>
<s> One would probably suffice in order to model issues of colour deficiency.  </s>
